elements

Class Alphabet

  • java.lang.Object
    • elements.Alphabet

  • public class Alphabet
extends java.lang.Object

    Class which define all the possible values for a Praat parameter or several praat parameter (specify it in the name).
    It will be use in the class manipulating sequences to give a value in a specific interval to the parameter. It wont be use directly, it will be use thought a meta alphabet, a GlobalAlphabet

    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Pierre-Yves Hervo
    See Also:
    GlobalAlphabet

    • Constructor Detail

      • Alphabet

        public Alphabet(java.lang.String name,
        double minBorn,
        double maxborn,
        int nbDigits)
         throws AlphabetException
        Public constructor wich allow to automaticly generate a double alphabet of length X with X the number of element beetween the minborn and the maxBorn You just have to precise the start value, the end value and the number of digits after the comma.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of your alphabet
        minBorn - the start value
        maxborn - the end value
        nbDigits - the number of digit for each number
        Throws:
        AlphabetException - if you enter twice the same value or if you put the higher value on the minBorn.
        Since:
        0.1
